Russian Equity Movers: Polymetal, Surgutneftegas, Tatneft

-- B y   J a s o n   C o r c o r a n
-- 
2011-04-26T15:41:01Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-26/russian-equity-movers-polymetal-surgutneftegas-tatneft.html
The 30-stock  Micex Index (INDEXCF)  declined
for the second day, losing 0.2 percent to 1,766.28 by the 6:45
p.m. close in Moscow. The dollar-denominated RTS Index added 0.1
percent to 2,033.32.  The following were among the most active stocks in the
Russian market today. Stock symbols are in parenthesis.  OAO Polymetal (PMTL RX), a Russian producer of gold and
silver, retreated for the first day in three, losing 2.2 percent
to 535.3 rubles after prices for the metal fell from record
highs.  OAO Surgutneftegas (SNGS RX) fell by its most in more than
a week, declining 0.9 percent to 29.28 rubles after the
government revokes tax breaks for its Talakan field in eastern
Siberia.  OAO  Tatneft (TATN)  (TATN3 RX), the Russian oil producer, slid for
a second day, retreating 0.7 percent to 183.26 rubles after it
said net income declined 14 percent last year from 2009 to 46.7
billion rubles ($1.67 billion), under international accounting
standards.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Gavin Serkin at 
 gserkin@bloomberg.net  